title: Is NYC’s COVID-19 Death Rate at Least 250x Higher Than Tokyo’s?
subtitle: A viral tweet from software engineer John McAfee raised questions about social-distancing measures during the coronavirus pandemic.
author: Jessica Lee
vclaim: As of April 25, 2020, the rate of people dying from the COVID-19 coronavirus disease in New York City was at least 250 times "higher" than Tokyo's — and growing with time.
